 Adelani Adepegba, Abuja The Police Service Commission has said it will prosecute candidates who tendered fake or forged credentials in the ongoing recruitment of 10,000 police constables. It explained that a candidate must satisfy some screening stages before he is considered suitable to join the Nigeria Police Force. These stages, it said, include medical screening, physical screening, written examination and authentication of certificates. This was contained in a statement by the PSC spokesman, Ikechukwu Ani, in Abuja on Monday. It said, â€œIt is also noteworthy to state that candidates discovered to have applied with or presented forged or fake certificates are not only disqualified but arrested and handed over to the Police for investigation and prosecution. Copyright PUNCH.
